searchData={"items":[{"type":"module","title":"ExQR","doc":"Pure Elixir QR code encoding library.\n\nSupports versions 1–20, error correction levels L/M/Q/H,\nand byte mode encoding. No external dependencies.","ref":"ExQR.html"},{"type":"module","title":"Usage - ExQR","doc":"{:ok, matrix, size} = ExQR.encode(\"https://example.com\")\n    {:ok, matrix, size} = ExQR.encode(\"Hello\", :h)\n\nThe matrix is a map of `{row, col} => 0 | 1` where 1 = black module.","ref":"ExQR.html#module-usage"},{"type":"module","title":"Converting to rows - ExQR","doc":"rows = ExQR.matrix_to_rows(matrix, size)\n    # => [[0, 1, 1, ...], [1, 0, 0, ...], ...]","ref":"ExQR.html#module-converting-to-rows"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.encode/2","doc":"Encode text into a QR code matrix.","ref":"ExQR.html#encode/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - ExQR.encode/2","doc":"- `text` — the string to encode\n  - `level` — error correction level: `:l`, `:m` (default), `:q`, or `:h`","ref":"ExQR.html#encode/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - ExQR.encode/2","doc":"`{:ok, matrix, size}` or `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"ExQR.html#encode/2-returns"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.encode!/2","doc":"Same as `encode/2` but raises on error.","ref":"ExQR.html#encode!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.matrix_to_rows/2","doc":"Convert a QR matrix to a list of lists (row-major).\n\nReturns `size` rows, each with `size` values (0 or 1).","ref":"ExQR.html#matrix_to_rows/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExQR.Encode","doc":"QR Code data encoding: mode selection, bit stream construction,\nerror correction block interleaving, and final codeword sequence.","ref":"ExQR.Encode.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Encode.encode/2","doc":"Encode text into the final codeword sequence (data + EC, interleaved).\n\nReturns `{:ok, version, codewords}` or `{:error, reason}`.","ref":"ExQR.Encode.html#encode/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExQR.GaloisField","doc":"GF(256) arithmetic for QR Code Reed-Solomon error correction.\n\nUses the primitive polynomial x^8 + x^4 + x^3 + x^2 + 1 (0x11D)\nwith generator α = 2. Exp and log tables are precomputed at compile time.","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.GaloisField.exp/1","doc":"Returns α^n in GF(256).","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html#exp/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.GaloisField.generator_polynomial/1","doc":"Generate a Reed-Solomon generator polynomial of given degree.","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html#generator_polynomial/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.GaloisField.log/1","doc":"Returns log_α(n) in GF(256). n must be > 0.","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html#log/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.GaloisField.multiply/2","doc":"Multiply two values in GF(256).","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html#multiply/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.GaloisField.multiply_polynomials/2","doc":"Multiply two polynomials over GF(256).","ref":"ExQR.GaloisField.html#multiply_polynomials/2"},{"type":"module","title":"ExQR.Matrix","doc":"QR Code matrix construction: function patterns, data placement,\nmasking, and format information.\n\nThe matrix is represented as a map of `{row, col} => value`\nwhere value is 0 (white) or 1 (black).","ref":"ExQR.Matrix.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Matrix.build/3","doc":"Build the final QR matrix for a given version, EC level, and codewords.\n\nReturns a `size × size` matrix as a map of `{row, col} => 0 | 1`.","ref":"ExQR.Matrix.html#build/3"},{"type":"module","title":"ExQR.ReedSolomon","doc":"Reed-Solomon error correction encoding for QR codes.\n\nComputes error correction codewords for a given data block\nusing polynomial division over GF(256).","ref":"ExQR.ReedSolomon.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.ReedSolomon.encode/2","doc":"Compute error correction codewords for a data block.","ref":"ExQR.ReedSolomon.html#encode/2"},{"type":"function","title":"Parameters - ExQR.ReedSolomon.encode/2","doc":"- `data` — list of data codeword integers (0–255)\n  - `ec_count` — number of error correction codewords to generate","ref":"ExQR.ReedSolomon.html#encode/2-parameters"},{"type":"function","title":"Returns - ExQR.ReedSolomon.encode/2","doc":"List of `ec_count` error correction codeword integers.","ref":"ExQR.ReedSolomon.html#encode/2-returns"},{"type":"module","title":"ExQR.Tables","doc":"QR Code version tables: data capacity, EC block structure,\nalignment pattern positions, and format/version information.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.alignment_positions/1","doc":"Alignment pattern center coordinates for a version.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#alignment_positions/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.char_count_bits/1","doc":"Character count indicator bit length for byte mode.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#char_count_bits/1"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.data_capacity/2","doc":"Total data codewords capacity for version and EC level.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#data_capacity/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.ec_info/2","doc":"Get EC block structure for version and level.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#ec_info/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.format_info/2","doc":"Get the 15-bit format information value.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#format_info/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.min_version/2","doc":"Find the smallest version that can hold `byte_count` bytes at `level`.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#min_version/2"},{"type":"function","title":"ExQR.Tables.size/1","doc":"QR code size in modules for a given version.","ref":"ExQR.Tables.html#size/1"},{"type":"extras","title":"ExQR","doc":"# ExQR\n\n[![Hex.pm](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/v/ex_qr.svg)](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_qr)\n[![Docs](https://img.shields.io/badge/docs-hexdocs-blue)](https://hexdocs.pm/ex_qr)\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/hexpm/l/ex_qr.svg)](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md)\n\nPure Elixir QR code encoding — versions 1–20, error correction levels\nL/M/Q/H, byte mode. No external dependencies.\n\nPart of the [ExPDF](https://hex.pm/packages/ex_pdf) umbrella.","ref":"readme.html"},{"type":"extras","title":"Installation - ExQR","doc":"```elixir\ndef deps do\n  [\n    {:ex_qr, \"~> 0.1\"}\n  ]\nend\n```","ref":"readme.html#installation"},{"type":"extras","title":"Usage - ExQR","doc":"```elixir\n{:ok, matrix, size} = ExQR.encode(\"https://example.com\")\n{:ok, matrix, size} = ExQR.encode(\"Hello\", :h)\n```\n\nThe matrix is a map of `{row, col} => 0 | 1` where `1` = black module.","ref":"readme.html#usage"},{"type":"extras","title":"Converting to rows - ExQR","doc":"```elixir\nrows = ExQR.matrix_to_rows(matrix, size)\n# => [[0, 1, 1, ...], [1, 0, 0, ...], ...]\n```","ref":"readme.html#converting-to-rows"},{"type":"extras","title":"Error correction levels - ExQR","doc":"- `:l` — Low (~7% recovery)\n- `:m` — Medium (~15% recovery, default)\n- `:q` — Quartile (~25% recovery)\n- `:h` — High (~30% recovery)","ref":"readme.html#error-correction-levels"},{"type":"extras","title":"License - ExQR","doc":"MIT. See [LICENSE.md](https://github.com/MisaelMa/ExPDF/blob/main/LICENSE.md).","ref":"readme.html#license"}],"proglang":"elixir","content_type":"text/markdown","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.2"}}